bdo:PaginationType
  a owl:Class ;
  rdfs:comment """Indicates whether the outlining is relative or absolute. This refers to the convention for WorkLocation information. Almost all outlining is done with absolute pagination.

Relative pagination uses pagination in the content of the work while absolute counts from the first image of a scanned volume an since there are 2 scanned pages of metadata in each volume, absolute pagination generally starts at 3."""@en ;
  rdfs:comment "Migration info: The pagination information affects the interpretation of the :WorkLocation(s) that occur in the original outline. The migration should add the pagination information to each WorkLocation since there will no longer be an Outline document"@en ;
  rdfs:label "pagination type"@en ;
.
PaginationType:
  a owl:Ontology ;
  owl:imports <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core> ;
  owl:versionInfo "Created with TopBraid Composer" ;
.
bdr:PaginationAbsolute
  a bdo:PaginationType ;
  skos:prefLabel "absolute pagination"@en ;
.
bdr:PaginationRelative
  a bdo:PaginationType ;
  skos:prefLabel "relative pagination"@en ;
.
